    h2 Raspberry Pi
    ul.fa-ul
      li 
        i.fa-li.fa.fa-wifi
        | 315Mhz Transmit/Receive Using Manchester Encoding
        ul.fa-ul
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00UWBJ7GK", target="_blank") Amazon modules
            | &nbsp;tested with Pi @ 3.3V.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | These are listed as 315 MHz but I received a 433 MHz module.
            | &nbsp;Range is not great but works for simple experimentation.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | To transmit data, a Manchester encoding must be used.  Manchester has no DC bias, so it's perfect for RF transmission.  The encoding encodes the two binary states as a low to high or high to low transition.  Another benefit of this is that it makes the encoding self-clocking.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | Receiver has automatic gain control (AGC).  When nothing is transmitting, the gain scales up generating a lot of amplified noise.  When a transmitter starts sending, the high gain rails the amplifier.  Transmit a preamble with alternating 1's and 0's to allow the AGC to adapt to the received power level before tranmitting real data.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="https://github.com/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/blob/master/amtel_manchester_coding.pdf") Documentation from Amtel on using Manchester encoding
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/test.sh") Script to test sending and receiving
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/rfwrite.c") Read from stdin and transmit
            | &nbsp;(support libraries:&nbsp;
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/manchester.h") manchester.h
            | ,&nbsp;
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/manchester.c") manchester.c
            | )
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/rfread.c") Receive and decode using a state machine
      li 
        i.fa-li.fa.fa-dashboard
        | DHT22 Temperature and Humidity Web-enabled Monitor
        ul.fa-ul
