          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="https://www.mathworks.com/help/thingspeak/update-channel-feed.html", target="_blank") ThingSpeak Documentation
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/readTemp.sh") Script to run the process
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="prettygit/nkundu/wiringpi-examples/master/dht22.c") Read one temperature and one humidity value
      li
        i.fa-li.fa.fa-wifi
        span IoT Research
        ul.fa-ul
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | The Expressif ESP8266 makes it easy to enable micros with WiFi and HTTP communication capability over a serial link.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | I used ESP-05 module connected to a U.FL antenna (
            a(a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00OSWCGVW", target="_blank") Amazon module
            | ,&nbsp;
            a(a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B004ZHT2JE", target="_blank") Amazon antenna
            | )
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | I don't think the ESP-05 is able to be flashed; the appropriate pin is not available on the header.  You need to ground GPIO0 to flash the firmware.
            | As of Fall, 2015, the stock firmware did not allow placing the ESP8266 into promiscuous mode, to capture all 802.11 activity, which was my original intent for this module. 
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | 470 uF cap across power supply helps on module boot.  Range was excellent with the external antenna mounted to a window.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            | You can communicate with this module using minicom, but you need to disbale the serial port console login.
          li
            i.fa-li.fa.fa-arrow-circle-right
            a(href="https://cdn.sparkfun.com/assets/learn_tutorials/4/0/3/4A-ESP8266__AT_Instruction_Set__EN_v0.30.pdf") Expressif ESP8266 AT Command Set


